quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,76,"You and your ancient forefathers?"
  26,77,"Indeed, they are enemies to me, except the Lord of the worlds,{1}",1:[The people worshipped idols in addition to Allāh.]
  26,78,"Who created me, and He [it is who] guides me."
  27,49,"They said, ",1:[i.e., the one responsible for executing his will and avenging his blood.]
  27,50,"And they planned a plan, and We planned a plan, while they perceived not."
  27,51,"Then look how was the outcome of their plan - that We destroyed them and their people, all."
  28,22,"And when he directed himself toward Madyan, he said, "
  28,23,"And when he came to the water [i.e., well] of Madyan, he found there a crowd of people watering [their flocks], and he found aside from them two women holding back [their flocks]. He said, "
  28,24,"So he watered [their flocks] for them; then he went back to the shade and said, "